WEBVTT

00:01.794 --> 00:04.295
So, Ed, l know recently you've been
having some anger

00:04.380 --> 00:07.965
over not being able to find a
post-retirement job. How's that going?

00:08.050 --> 00:13.137
l worked 45 years supervising
200 people in waste management.

00:13.222 --> 00:16.724
And l can't even get a job
as a Walmart greeter.

00:16.809 --> 00:21.813
And they hire handicaps
and whatever else tumbles off the short bus.

00:22.940 --> 00:25.608
l'd like to say something
as a person with a job.

00:25.693 --> 00:27.193
You're lucky not to have one.

00:27.277 --> 00:30.321
l'd trade places with you in a second if
you weren't a creepy old man.

00:31.407 --> 00:33.533
lt sounds like you're having
some issues with your newjob, Lacey.

00:33.617 --> 00:34.659
You want to talk about it?

00:34.743 --> 00:38.496
lt's bad enough that my mother makes me
work to get my trust fund check,

00:38.580 --> 00:41.165
but the job starts in the morning.

00:41.250 --> 00:44.460
Have you ever woken up in the morning?

00:44.545 --> 00:47.922
lt's horrible. The sun's in the wrong place.

00:49.758 --> 00:52.844
You may not believe this, but most people

00:52.928 --> 00:55.805
wake up in the morning
and go to bed at night.

00:55.889 --> 00:59.892
lt started in the '40s, when they were
rationing daylight during World War ll.

01:00.769 --> 01:03.146
The worst part is sitting in traffic for hours.

01:03.230 --> 01:06.566
lt's like waiting in line at a club,
except when you get to the end,

01:06.650 --> 01:10.862
there's no dancing. There's just me,
selling blush at Sephora.

01:10.946 --> 01:14.198
Ain't nothing gonna fix that face, bitch.

01:14.324 --> 01:16.284
After they buy makeup from you,
they buy clothes from me.

01:16.368 --> 01:18.619
Nothing is gonna fix those hips, bitch.

01:19.288 --> 01:21.122
Then the bitch comes home to me.

01:23.625 --> 01:26.586
And l have to pay the credit card bill.

01:27.796 --> 01:29.547
And that's how America works.

01:31.133 --> 01:33.760
Well, great session, everybody.
See you all tomorrow.

01:33.844 --> 01:37.638
l just realized l'm not a part
of how America works.

01:43.061 --> 01:44.812
Hey, Lacey. Before you go,

01:44.897 --> 01:47.857
l'm worried about how
rush hour traffic might affect you.

01:47.941 --> 01:49.025
How have you been dealing with that?

01:49.109 --> 01:52.153
Pretty well. l just take it out on all
the other drivers around me.

01:53.155 --> 01:56.449
Yesterday l bumper-tapped a
minivan into an intersection.

01:57.659 --> 02:00.828
You're on probation. lf you get arrested
for road rage, they will put you in prison.

02:00.913 --> 02:03.790
l know. l should probably
see somebody about that.

02:04.124 --> 02:06.667
Lacey, where are you right now?

02:07.336 --> 02:09.086
l'm...

02:10.464 --> 02:12.298
Okay.

02:15.052 --> 02:17.220
How about l go out driving with you
in the morning traffic?

02:17.304 --> 02:20.181
l can show you some techniques,
how to diffuse your anger on the road.

02:20.516 --> 02:22.558
Okay. Pick me up at 9:00.

02:22.643 --> 02:24.143
No, no, no. You're going to drive.

02:24.603 --> 02:25.937
ln that traffic?

02:28.690 --> 02:31.192
Hey, we've got to figure out
a schedule for your dad's visit.

02:31.276 --> 02:33.444
Dad's visit? Who's he visiting?

02:33.529 --> 02:35.738
Us, you, tomorrow.

02:36.073 --> 02:37.824
-What?
-He didn't call you?

02:37.908 --> 02:40.326
He's been calling all week,
but l didn't answer.

02:40.410 --> 02:42.745
Not talking to him is so much easier
if l don't pick up the phone.

02:44.915 --> 02:47.750
Well, he's coming in tomorrow
and he's staying with you.

02:48.627 --> 02:51.671
Of course he's coming now. You know why?
He knows l'm happy.

02:51.755 --> 02:54.131
He can smell it all the way from Ohio.

02:54.466 --> 02:58.135
Maybe he just wants to see you.
You know, he's getting older.

02:58.220 --> 02:59.679
He's not gonna be around forever.

02:59.763 --> 03:01.681
Stop trying to cheer me up.

03:07.020 --> 03:10.022
Wow. Candles. Romantic.

03:10.399 --> 03:12.149
lt's not what we do.

03:13.235 --> 03:14.360
This is purely sexual.

03:14.444 --> 03:17.989
l just read a study about
which smells increase male arousal.

03:18.448 --> 03:22.159
This one's vanilla, that one's cinnamon,
that one's donut.

03:23.120 --> 03:25.746
lt smells like a stripper
standing in a Krispy Kreme.

03:27.082 --> 03:28.624
l like it.

03:36.258 --> 03:39.260
l don't want to see my father.
ls that so horrible?

03:40.178 --> 03:43.389
Well, if you're imagining him right now, it is.

03:44.683 --> 03:47.393
He drives me nuts.
l don't want him in my house.

03:47.686 --> 03:50.271
Let's take a moment and get past this.

03:50.981 --> 03:53.524
Okay. lf l were your father,
what would you say to me right now?

03:54.151 --> 03:57.111
Dad, that's not the bra you usually wear.

03:58.322 --> 03:59.780
Come on, serious. What would you say?

04:00.115 --> 04:02.700
l wouldn't say anything
because he doesn't listen.

04:02.784 --> 04:05.745
He just criticizes.
He shows no affection whatsoever.

04:05.829 --> 04:07.872
The guy's never hugged me.
l can't do right by him.

04:07.956 --> 04:09.832
l can't talk to him. l can't...

04:10.292 --> 04:12.668
l can't breathe.

04:13.295 --> 04:17.590
Okay. You're hyperventilating.
Put your head between your knees.

04:19.009 --> 04:21.093
-lt's not working.
-Okay.

04:21.178 --> 04:23.220
Put your head between my knees.

04:24.306 --> 04:26.474
That only relaxes you.

04:29.728 --> 04:33.481
Hey, Charlie. l got us tickets to take
your dad to the Dodger game on Friday.

04:33.565 --> 04:34.565
Does that sound good?

04:34.650 --> 04:37.610
Great. We can get him one of those giant
foam hands to poke me with

04:37.694 --> 04:40.571
when he reminds me
how l screwed up my baseball career.

04:40.656 --> 04:43.324
"The catcher could have been you." Poke.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.912
Will you stop anticipating problems?

04:47.996 --> 04:51.290
l don't anticipate problems with my dad.
l anticipate disasters.

04:51.667 --> 04:55.336
You watch. He'll walk through
that door, won't even acknowledge me.

04:55.420 --> 04:58.506
And then no matter what l do,
he'll find a way to complain about it.

04:58.632 --> 05:00.675
That's a problem, not a disaster.

05:01.009 --> 05:04.512
No, it will be when he destroys
everything with his heat vision.

05:05.347 --> 05:06.722
ls Grandpa here yet?

05:06.807 --> 05:07.932
Not yet, honey.

05:08.016 --> 05:11.185
You know, l don't think l've ever hung out
with you and Grandpa at the same time.

05:11.269 --> 05:12.895
Maybe they're the same person.

05:12.980 --> 05:15.064
Don't even joke about that.

05:20.487 --> 05:22.113
Charlie!

05:22.197 --> 05:23.781
Oh, all right.

05:30.831 --> 05:31.872
Charlie.

05:32.165 --> 05:33.374
Hey, Dad.

05:34.042 --> 05:35.209
Come here.

05:39.172 --> 05:40.589
Here you go, Dad.

05:40.716 --> 05:42.133
lmported, huh?

05:42.217 --> 05:45.678
l know you like Bud, but l've been so
busy working the past few days,

05:45.762 --> 05:47.096
l didn't have time to go to the store.

05:47.180 --> 05:49.223
You know l don't like imported beer,

05:50.517 --> 05:52.893
but this is delicious. Thank you, Charlie.

05:56.773 --> 05:58.649
-And now, to you.
-Yes.

05:58.734 --> 06:01.569
You know, every time l see you,
you get more and more beautiful.

06:02.237 --> 06:05.406
Martin, l used to think
you were a shameless flirt,

06:05.490 --> 06:07.658
but now l know you're just telling the truth.

06:09.036 --> 06:11.537
l always thought Charlie was an idiot
for letting you get away.

06:11.872 --> 06:12.913
Here we go.

06:12.998 --> 06:16.000
But you two seem happier now
than when you were married.

06:16.585 --> 06:18.294
You're a good man, Charlie Goodson.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.755
You took a bad situation
and you made it work.

06:21.673 --> 06:22.757
And?

06:23.675 --> 06:25.593
And l'm proud of you.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.389
Sam, why don't you show me
where l'm bunking?

06:30.474 --> 06:31.849
All right.

06:32.601 --> 06:34.894
-Good night, Dad.
-Good night.

06:34.978 --> 06:38.481
lt's so good to see you. Both of you.

06:44.863 --> 06:46.280
Good night, guys.

06:46.364 --> 06:48.365
Good night.

06:50.035 --> 06:51.702
l know how this story ends.

06:51.787 --> 06:54.955
l call his wife in Ohio and she says,
"How can you be with your father?

06:55.040 --> 06:56.874
"He died five years ago."

07:00.462 --> 07:03.130
l'm not buying it.
Nobody changes that much.

07:03.215 --> 07:04.715
Maybe he's mellowed out.

07:04.800 --> 07:07.676
You're a therapist. You're supposed to
believe that human beings can change.

07:07.761 --> 07:09.595
l do believe that human beings can change.

07:09.679 --> 07:11.806
None of that applies to my father.

07:12.516 --> 07:14.141
l think you're overreacting.

07:14.476 --> 07:15.726
l'll prove it to you.

07:15.811 --> 07:18.729
He's not just critical of me. He'll come down
on anybody who disagrees with him.

07:18.814 --> 07:22.108
Religion, politics, he'll always find a way
to make it feel like you're wrong.

07:22.275 --> 07:23.609
Charlie, l don't want to be a part of this.

07:23.693 --> 07:25.402
Something smells good.

07:26.363 --> 07:28.906
-Good morning.
-Good morning, Dad. Sit down.

07:28.990 --> 07:31.575
l made breakfast. Coffee's brewing.
This is my neighbor, Michael.

07:31.660 --> 07:33.911
-Michael, good to meet you.
-You, too.

07:33.995 --> 07:36.080
We were just talking about how active
you were in the unions.

07:36.164 --> 07:39.667
Yes, indeed. Unions are the foundation
of the middle class.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.836
