15:21.004 --> 15:23.130
"Here's looking at you, kid."

15:25.925 --> 15:29.011
So, that girl you're sleeping with,

15:29.095 --> 15:32.306
the one you have no intention of marrying.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.224
lt's that therapist, am l right?

15:34.309 --> 15:35.392
How did you know?

15:35.476 --> 15:36.977
l didn't until just now.

15:38.813 --> 15:42.232
Anyway, if you're not going to
remarry Jennifer, which you should,

15:42.317 --> 15:45.819
you should seriously consider
making an honest woman out of Kate.

15:46.487 --> 15:49.114
She's more fun as a dishonest woman.

15:49.198 --> 15:52.034
Let me tell you something, son.
Your dear mother, may God rest her soul...

15:52.118 --> 15:54.369
She's not dead. Quit saying that.

15:54.454 --> 15:55.996
She's remarried and living in Tampa.

15:56.080 --> 15:59.958
l don't keep track.
Anyway, she reminds me a lot of Kate.

16:00.585 --> 16:03.170
A lot to handle, but well worth it.

16:04.130 --> 16:05.839
Well, here's to difficult women.

16:05.923 --> 16:07.841
And the men who cannot handle them.

16:10.678 --> 16:13.639
This is my 1 0th birthday.
That's my dad and my brother.

16:13.931 --> 16:15.599
That's me on the end.

16:15.683 --> 16:19.269
You're lucky. My family never made
any home movies with me.

16:19.354 --> 16:22.898
l was the fourth kid.
My father was fond of saying

16:22.982 --> 16:25.150
l was the fourth of three.

16:25.443 --> 16:27.027
Hey, l can always photoshop you into mine.

16:27.654 --> 16:31.198
Here, Charlie, we got you a 45-year-old
bald man for your birthday.

16:31.282 --> 16:32.491
His stories are kind of a bummer,

16:32.575 --> 16:33.992
but they'll make you feel better
about your own life.

16:37.038 --> 16:39.081
You don't have to do that.

16:40.708 --> 16:43.085
l just can't get over how young l...

16:43.795 --> 16:45.045
Hold on.

16:45.797 --> 16:46.880
What?

16:50.051 --> 16:51.968
That woman with her back to us.

16:52.053 --> 16:53.345
Yeah?

16:53.429 --> 16:56.348
That's my Aunt Cecile.
My dad said she died a year before this.

16:56.599 --> 17:00.102
Good for her. lt looks like she's almost
completely recovered from her death.

17:01.437 --> 17:02.854
Oh, my God, l was right. l'm not crazy.

17:02.939 --> 17:04.940
My dad really is a terrible person.

17:05.566 --> 17:06.983
Congratulations.

17:07.068 --> 17:08.235
Thank you.

17:11.322 --> 17:12.781
l'm really glad you're driving me, Ed.

17:12.865 --> 17:14.741
l'm going to show up
at work so much more relaxed.

17:14.867 --> 17:17.452
My pleasure, Miss Daisy.

17:17.537 --> 17:20.372
l don't know if l ever told you,
but a long time ago, l used to drive...

17:20.456 --> 17:22.958
Don't let that girl in! Don't let her in!
Why'd you let her in?

17:23.042 --> 17:27.254
Because she had her blinker on
and she smiled at me. l'm a sucker for that.

17:28.339 --> 17:30.006
Quick, that lane's open! Go, go, go, go!

17:30.091 --> 17:32.426
That is not a lane. That's a shoulder!

17:32.510 --> 17:33.885
That's for emergencies.

17:33.970 --> 17:35.262
Well, you're going to need
to go to the hospital

17:35.346 --> 17:36.555
if you don't pick up the pace!

17:36.639 --> 17:39.683
l knew this was not a good idea.
l'm warning you,

17:39.767 --> 17:41.852
one more word out of you,
just one more word...

17:41.936 --> 17:43.145
Yeah, whatcha gonna do?

17:43.229 --> 17:44.604
That's it!

17:51.279 --> 17:53.613
Screw you! My driver left.

17:54.323 --> 17:55.907
Ed?

17:59.537 --> 18:01.037
-Hey, Charlie.
-Hey, Dad.

18:01.539 --> 18:03.540
-Can l get you a beer?
-Sure. What do you got?

18:03.624 --> 18:06.168
Well, let's see.

18:06.252 --> 18:09.880
l've got "dirty filthy liar,"

18:09.964 --> 18:11.965
"my dad's a bastard,"

18:13.634 --> 18:15.844
and a lager from Holland.

18:17.138 --> 18:19.055
Still haven't gotten any Bud Light, huh?

18:19.140 --> 18:22.142
There he is. Hi, Dad.

18:28.232 --> 18:29.733
Okay.

18:30.651 --> 18:31.651
What happened?

18:32.445 --> 18:35.530
You told me Aunt Cecile died
when l was nine.

18:35.615 --> 18:38.492
l've got home movies of her
at my 1 0th birthday.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.494
Sitting at the table when
l blew out the candles.

18:42.830 --> 18:44.998
Was she moving?

18:46.918 --> 18:49.753
Just enough to get her
beer mug to her face.

18:49.837 --> 18:51.505
So, l lied about one little thing.

18:51.589 --> 18:56.968
No, you didn't. l found my report card
from the year you smashed my guitar.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.679
My grades, they never dropped.

18:59.764 --> 19:03.809
And l talked to Mom.
You traded the puppy for a power drill.

19:04.018 --> 19:07.979
Well, at least the dog didn't die.
l mean, l'm sure he's dead now, but...

19:09.524 --> 19:12.359
Why did you come here?
Why are you being so nice?

19:12.443 --> 19:13.944
What do you want?

19:14.028 --> 19:18.448
l want to leave Ohio.
There's nothing left there for me.

19:18.533 --> 19:21.451
All my friends are gone,

19:21.536 --> 19:24.454
and your siblings
won't have anything to do with me.

19:24.539 --> 19:26.039
What about your wife?

19:26.791 --> 19:29.000
Corinne left me last month.

19:31.128 --> 19:33.964
And if it will make you feel any better,
she took my puppy.

19:34.841 --> 19:36.591
So now you're a puppy guy?

19:36.676 --> 19:39.177
Charlie, look.

19:40.263 --> 19:43.723
l want to move out here
and l want to live with you.

19:44.934 --> 19:47.018
You act like a jerk my whole life,
then lie about it,

19:47.103 --> 19:48.603
now you want me to take you in?

19:48.688 --> 19:54.067
l really need some help, see, because l don't
have enough money left to live on my own.

19:55.653 --> 19:59.155
And if l could do anything
about the past, l would.

19:59.240 --> 20:00.574
Hell, you know l tried.

20:01.534 --> 20:06.580
And it would have worked, too, if it hadn't
been for the boozy ghost ofAunt Cecile.

20:08.249 --> 20:12.085
Look, l'll do the best l can from here on.
That's all l can promise.

20:13.087 --> 20:14.796
-One last thing.
-Anything.

20:14.881 --> 20:16.673
-And l need the truth.
-You bet.

20:17.884 --> 20:19.259
Did Mom really leave you

20:19.343 --> 20:21.845
or did you trade her to that guy
in Tampa for a belt sander?

20:23.931 --> 20:26.433
No, actually, it was a leaf blower.

20:31.355 --> 20:34.858
Don't get too hard on yourself.
Your dad fooled us both.

20:36.235 --> 20:39.446
l think it's really sweet that
you're getting him his own place out here.

20:39.530 --> 20:41.197
Yeah, it's in a really nice area.

20:41.282 --> 20:44.451
He just has to decide if
he wants to be a Blood or a Crip.

20:46.287 --> 20:48.455
-Charlie.
-l'm kidding, kidding.

20:48.539 --> 20:49.998
lt's about 20 minutes away.

20:50.082 --> 20:52.918
Just far enough so he can't just walk
over here whenever he wants.

20:53.461 --> 20:56.963
At least now l know what you'll look
like in your 70s.

20:57.632 --> 21:01.134
Based on your dad's looks,
l could still be doing you.

21:01.344 --> 21:02.469
Thanks.

21:02.553 --> 21:05.263
Hey, you got a picture of your mom
so l can see what l might be getting into?

21:05.556 --> 21:07.474
Actually, l look more like my dad.

21:08.309 --> 21:10.393
But if it makes you feel any better,

21:10.478 --> 21:12.145
he's got an ass that won't quit.
